Bank of Canada increases the overnight policy rate by 0.25% to 5%... the highest isn't been since March 2001. Canadian banks respond by increasing their prime lending rate to 7.2%.
.
Inflation won't reach 2% until mid-2025 so the elevated interest will remain elevated longer than anticipated.
.

As of July 17th, Real Estate Boards in the Lower Mainland will be implementing a new multiple offer disclosure form (Disclosure of Multiple Offers Presented).
.
This form will list all of the competing offers received and the name of the submitting brokerage. 
. 
The listing Realtor will then need to provide it to the buyer‚Äôs agents as well as to any unrepresented buyers who submitted offers, no later than one calendar day after the seller has decided on all the presented offers. 
.

Located within blocks of Main St, this sunny southwest facing corner home with over-height ceilings features a kitchen with a blend of white and wood cabinetry complimented by stone counter-tops and S/S appliances (5-burner gas range) opening onto the dining room & spacious living room - don't forget the convenient powder room. Upstairs you'll find 3 beds (rare for the area) & 2 more bathrooms. Relax on your massive 389 sqft roof top deck with Downtown/Mountain views & a gas connection perfect for a BBQ or fire table. reel_29_text:
Welcome to the GOLDEN MILE, one of Vancouver's most sought after addresses within walking distance to Jericho Beach/Tennis Club, Royal Vancouver Yacht Club and W 4th Avenue with its shopping and restaurants. This FULL DUPLEX (3566 & 3568) has identical sides with each featuring a living room with large, bright bay windows, a designated dining room, kitchen with breakfast bar and a powder room on the main floor. On the upper level you'll find a spacious Master Bedroom with vaulted ceilings and a 2nd Bedroom with its own private balcony. Make your way up to the massive Roof Top Deck to soak up the sun, entertain and enjoy English Bay water views. Both sides have their own private single car garage and ample storage in crawl space.

üí•Another Home SOLDüí•

Two more Acepted Offers this week! The mass media will tell you that the Real Estate Market in Vancouver is flat, however this is far from the truth!

Yes sales, listings and prices are declining overall but that is welcome news for Buyers! We have helped numerous clients over the past few months add to their portfolio, increase their net worth and jump into the detached market. Prices are down and we are negotiating some unbelievable deals.

For Sellers, there are still buyers going around and making offers! This home was previously listed with another agent and failed to sell. However, with our proven selling strategies and superior property marketing we were able to secure a buyer for a favorable price.

Are you looking to sell and get the most for your home? Are you looking to buy and get a great deal on your next home? Great! Give us a call today to help you successfully navigate the Market.

post_27_text:
Where heritage meets modern. This stunning home in the heart upper Kitsilano has been beautifully updated and boasts an incredible open concept main floor, perfect for entertainers. The spacious and bright living room features Mansana stone fireplaces, adding a touch of elegance and warmth. The wood banister, wainscoting, and crown moldings further accentuate the home.  Hardwood floors, soaring ceiling heights, and incredible natural light make this home feel open and spacious. 

Step down into the modern and spacious kitchen equipped with integrated Miele appliances making it the perfect space for intimate meals or entertaining guests. From the family room, step out into the mature, south facing garden offering a tranquil and serene space to relax.

The home boasts three bedrooms upstairs, each with their own unique character and charm and one bedroom downstairs for guests or potential suite. The massive crawlspace is perfect for additional storage, making it easy to keep the home organized and clutter-free. New roof and EV charging. The single car garage, in addition to the parking pad, provides ample parking for multiple vehicles. 

Located in a fantastic generational community just steps away from the Arbutus Greenway, providing easy access to beautiful parks, jogging and cycling paths, and the new Broadway line. The neighborhood is home to fantastic coffee shops, restaurants, and shopping, making it easy to enjoy the best of Vancouver‚Äôs vibrant culture. Its location, in one of Vancouver‚Äôs most sought after neighbourhoods, close to parks, shops, and restaurants, makes it an ideal place to call home. 

2048 W 13TH Ave | 4 bed | 3 bath | 2400 ft.¬≤ | garage + EV | 3 patios | suite potential | Offered at $2,498,000

Where heritage meets modern. This stunning home in the heart upper Kitsilano has been beautifully updated and boasts an incredible open concept main floor, perfect for entertainers. The spacious and bright living room features Mansana stone fireplaces, adding a touch of elegance and warmth. The wood banister, wainscoting, and crown moldings further accentuate the home. Hardwood floors, soaring ceiling heights, and incredible natural light make this home feel open and spacious.

Step down into the modern and spacious kitchen equipped with integrated Miele appliances making it the perfect space for intimate meals or entertaining guests. From the family room, step out into the mature, south facing garden offering a tranquil and serene space to relax.

The home boasts three bedrooms upstairs, each with their own unique character and charm and one bedroom downstairs for guests or potential suite. The massive crawlspace is perfect for additional storage, making it easy to keep the home organized and clutter-free. New roof and EV charging. The single car garage, in addition to the parking pad, provides ample parking for multiple vehicles.

Located in a fantastic generational community just steps away from the Arbutus Greenway, providing easy access to beautiful parks, jogging and cycling paths, and the new Broadway line. The neighborhood is home to fantastic coffee shops, restaurants, and shopping, making it easy to enjoy the best of Vancouver‚Äôs vibrant culture. Its location, in one of Vancouver‚Äôs most sought after neighbourhoods, close to parks, shops, and restaurants, makes it an ideal place to call home.

reel_30_text:
MARKET UPDATE

The seasons are changing in Metro Vancouver, and as the days are getting hotter, the housing market is too! Home sales in March 2021 set new records, with an incredible 126.1% increase over the sales numbers in March 2020.

These impressive figures are no surprise. After a year where we‚Äôve all spent more time than ever at home, buyers are looking for thoughtful layouts and increased square-footage to accommodate work spaces, growing kids, and outdoor leisure. Those needs add up to a competitive market for buyers, and an incredible opportunity for sellers.

Here are some more highlights from the latest REBGV report:

Record-breaking home sales. There were 5,708 home sales in March, a 53.2% increase over last month and a 72.2% increase over the 10 year average. The sales-to-active listings ratio is 62.4%, indicating a very strong seller‚Äôs market.
Rural and suburban regions are especially hot. Delta-South almost doubled its demand over 2020, with an196% increase in sales. Whistler and Squamish are close behind.
Prices are increasing. The heightened activity is driving prices up, especially for single-family homes and townhomes. The average price of a detached home is $1.7 million, up almost 18% from March 2020, and townhomes are averaging $872,000, up 10.4% since March 2020.
Listings are scarce. Even though last month saw a record-breaking 8,287 new listings added to the market, demand is so high that total listings are down from previous years. Currently there are 9,145 homes for sale, almost 5% lower than last March and 18.6% below the 10-year March average.

Looking to sell your home, or buy a space that fulfills your desires and fits your lifestyle? Let‚Äôs talk! I‚Äôm ready to lend my expertise and insights to helping you find the perfect place to call home.
